Sentiment Analysis

In [5]:
positive = 0
negative = 0
neutral = 0
polarity = 0
tweet_list = []
neutral_list = []
negative_list = []
positive_list = []
tweet_geo=[]
    

def percentage(part,whole):
 return 100 * float(part)/float(whole)

for tweet_f in tweets:
    tweet_list.append(tweet_f.text)
    tweet_geo.append(tweet_f.user.location)
    analysis = TextBlob(tweet_f.text)
    score = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer().polarity_scores(tweet_f.text)
    neg = score['neg']
    neu = score['neu']
    pos = score['pos']
    comp = score['compound']
    polarity += analysis.sentiment.polarity
     
    if neg > pos:
        negative_list.append(tweet_f.text)
        negative += 1
    elif pos > neg:
        positive_list.append(tweet_f.text)
        positive += 1
 
    elif pos == neg:
        neutral_list.append(tweet_f.text)
        neutral += 1
     
positive = percentage(positive, no_of_Tweets)
negative = percentage(negative, no_of_Tweets)
neutral = percentage(neutral, no_of_Tweets)
polarity = percentage(polarity, no_of_Tweets)
positive = format(positive, '.1f')
negative = format(negative, '.1f')
neutral = format(neutral, '.1f')

In [14]:
processed_text = lambda x: re.sub("(@[A-Za-z09]+)|([^0-9A-Za-z \t])|(\w+:\/\/\S+)"," ",x)
tweets = tweepy.Cursor(api.search, q=keyword, count =200, lang='en').items(no_of_Tweets)

tweets_copy =[]

for tweet in tweets:
    tweets_copy.append(tweet)




tweets_df = pd.DataFrame()

for tweet in tweets_copy:
    hashtags = []
    try:
        for hashtag in tweet.entities["hashtags"]:
            hashtags.append(hashtag["text"])
        text = api.get_status(id=tweet.id, tweet_mode='extended').full_text
    except:
        pass
    tweets_df = tweets_df.append(pd.DataFrame({'user_name': tweet.user.name, 
                                               'user_location': tweet.user.location,\
                                               'user_description': tweet.user.description,
                                               'user_verified': tweet.user.verified,
                                               'date': tweet.created_at,
                                               'text': text, 
                                               'hashtags': [hashtags if hashtags else None],
                                               'source': tweet.source}))
    tweets_df = tweets_df.reset_index(drop=True)

def plot_percentage(feature, title, df):
    fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize = (20,10))
    g=sns.countplot(df[feature], order = df[feature].value_counts().index[:20], palette = 'Set3')
    g.set_title("Number of percentage of {}".format(title))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90, size =10)
    plt.show()
    
 
tweets_df.user_location.replace('','unknown location', inplace = True)


plot_percentage("user_location", "countries", tweets_df)   
plot_percentage("source", "sources", tweets_df)
